#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:4
msgid ":index:`AC3 Files <configuration; ac3 tag options>`"
msgstr ":index:`AC3-bestanden <configuratie; opties voor AC3-tags>`"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:9
msgid ""
"Picard can save APEv2 tags to pure AC3 files, which by default do not "
"support tagging. APEv2 tags in AC3 are supported by some players, but "
"players not supporting AC3 files with APEv2 tags can have issues loading and "
"playing those files. To deal with this you can choose whether to save tags "
"to those files:"
msgstr ""
"Picard kan APEv2-tags opslaan in pure AC3-bestanden, die standaard geen tags "
"ondersteunen. APEv2-tags in AC3 worden door sommige spelers ondersteund, "
"maar spelers die dit niet ondersteunen, hebben vaak problemen met het laden "
"van zulke bestanden. Om dit op te lossen, kan je kiezen of je tags in die "
"bestanden opslaat:"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:11
msgid "**Save APEv2 tags**"
msgstr "**APEv2-tags opslaan**"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:13
msgid "Picard will save APEv2 tags to the files."
msgstr "Picard slaat APEv2-tags in de bestanden op."

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:15
msgid "**Do not save tags**"
msgstr "**Geen tags opslaan**"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:17
msgid ""
"Picard will not save any tags to the files, but you can still use Picard to "
"rename them. By default existing APEv2 tags will be kept in the file."
msgstr ""
"Picard slaat geen tags in AAC-bestanden op, maar je kan Picard nog wel "
"gebruiken om die bestanden te hernoemen. Standaard worden bestaande APEv2-"
"tags behouden."

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:19
msgid "**Remove APEv2 tags**"
msgstr "**APEv2-tags verwijderen**"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:21
msgid ""
"If you have \"Do not save tags\" enabled checking this option will cause "
"Picard to remove existing APEv2 tags from the file on saving."
msgstr ""
"Als je de optie ‘Geen tags opslaan’ hebt ingeschakeld en je deze optie "
"aanvinkt, verwijdert Picard bestaande APEv2-tags tijdens het opslaan uit de "
"bestanden."

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_ac3.rst:23
msgid ""
"Regardless of how you have configured saving tags Picard will always read "
"existing APEv2 tags in AC3 files."
msgstr ""
"Hoe je deze opties ook hebt ingesteld, Picard zal bestaande APEv2-tags in "
"AC3-bestanden wel lezen."
